  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Factory Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>E3 Design Pte Ltd specializes in commercial outfitting. E3 offers valued clients a comprehensive suite of services from design consultancy, project management, design, and build to interior fit-out.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead and manage daily production operations to deliver high-quality furniture and wood products on schedule. Oversee the entire manufacturing process while collaborating with cross-functional teams to meet project specifications and client expectations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Plan and coordinate daily production activities to ensure timely delivery of furniture and wood products that meet client requirements</li><li>Inspect finished products to verify compliance with design specifications, safety standards, and quality benchmarks</li><li>Supervise the full production lifecycle including material cutting, assembly, finishing, and on-site installation to optimize workflow and output quality</li><li>Lead, train, and schedule carpenters, foremen, and technicians to maintain a skilled and efficient workforce</li><li>Monitor inventory levels and maintain machinery such as routers, planners, and edge-bending machines to ensure operational efficiency and minimize material wastage</li><li>Collaborate with designers, clients, and contractors to align production processes with project requirements and resolve any issues proactively</li><li>Interpret blueprints, technical drawings, and specifications to guide production and ensure accuracy</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Possess at least a Higher Nitec or Diploma in Engineering, Manufacturing, or a related field</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in furniture manufacturing and construction</li><li>Strong knowledge of carpentry, woodworking techniques, and operation of woodworking machinery</li><li>Effective interpersonal skills to manage teams and maintain client relationships</li><li>Proficiency in production planning tools or inventory management systems</li></ul>",
